}},"metadata":{"altText":"","workURN":"","caption":"<p>This figure shows the percentage of U.S. firms making payouts to shareholders. The shaded regions show the firms that used dividends exclusively (<em>blue</em>), repurchases exclusively (<em>green</em>), or both (<em>red</em>&#x2009;). Because firms that repurchase shares do not usually do so every year, we classify a firm as using repurchases if it repurchased that year or the previous year. Note that after steadily declining for more than 20&#xA0;years, dividend use has been on the rise since 2000. However, as <a class=\"xref\" href=\"m166_ch17lev1sec3.xhtml#x0278\">Figure 17.6</a> shows, repurchases now account for the largest part of the total value of distributions.</p>","alfrescoPath":"bronte-e2e-testing-qaint/documentLibrary/BV E2E Test/[10-05-2022] Berk","originalAssetName":"FG_17_005.jpg","longDesc":"","height":"555"}},{"urn":"urn:aero:caab9940-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f","asset":{"assetProvider":"ALFRESCO","id":"caab9940-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f","assetMediaType":"image","assetVisibility":"GLOBAL","ownerId":"e88133a0-8dc4-11eb-964e-4d7e264c9958","subscriptionId":"f0afd4d0-d2ff-11ea-9998-d57e1e28aca1","alfrescoId":"23b1708a-c129-49a6-8a9a-c95467dd2cfa","name":"FG_17_006.jpg","version":"2.0","lastModifiedDate":1664998392,"lastSyncDate":1665085925},"source":{"small":{"width":511,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/caab9940-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/small/3d126adcc75ab9b220260f569853b7de.jpeg","height":300},"original":{"width":1022,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/caab9940-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/medium/3d126adcc75ab9b220260f569853b7de.jpeg","height":600},"medium":{"width":1022,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/caab9940-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/medium/3d126adcc75ab9b220260f569853b7de.jpeg","height":600},"thumb":{"width":255,"url":"https://assets-bronte-qaint.pearson.com/caab9940-44e0-11ed-82a0-5b736ba8ac7f/thumb/3d126adcc75ab9b220260f569853b7de.jpeg","heig